	(text "* If the board is powered through the RAW pin the VCC pin can be used as an output.\n* 7.3V is programmed to cater for the drop on the Schottky diode thus the voltage to\n   the RAW pin of Pro-Micro is approximately 7V"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 24.892 253.238 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 2.159 2.159)
				(thickness 0.2223)
			)
			(justify left)
		)
		(uuid "f82189a5-0d34-4b60-97b2-c399789103ba")
	)
	(text "* Half duplex: Either transmitting or receiving\n  data at a particular time.\n\n* R: Data Output\n* D: Data Input\n* DE has internal pull-down (driver disabled by default).\n* RE has internal pull-up (receiver disabled by default)."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
